# Create Documentation

When asked to create new documentation, read and follow the skill at `.claude/skills/docs-create/SKILL.md`.

Key points:
- Read `docs/guidelines.md` for style and structure rules before writing.
- Use a template when one exists (`docs/templates/frontend-template.md`, `backend-template.md`, or `package-template.md`).
- For ADRs, check if the target package has its own template in `packages/<pkg>/docs/adr/`.
- For doc types without a template, follow the general structure guidance in the guidelines.
- No placeholder text may remain in the final doc.
- Omit template sections that don't apply — no "Not applicable" filler.
